title: For Sale:  RARE Early Fitz conversion Nickel plated Colt Police Positive 38 Special
postcontent:
RARE Early Fitz conversion Nickel plated Colt Police Positive 38 Special
S# 69XXX (1913) with early Rampant Colt superimposed over the stylized "C", grooved hammer top, original barrel cut to 2 1/8” according to information pass on to me from Colt collector this was shipped to California in 1913.
This Fitz conversion was done at some point much later than the gun production date and after Fitz conversions already became known and popular. This was probably done between 1920 and 1925 because of the patina. The workmanship on this old Colt looks like it was done by a Master gunsmith that paid attention to detail.
 
Bore and rifling are in good condition along with the cylinder, its chamber for 38 special you can also use the shorter 38 S&W cartridge.  Pistol has period grips and the nickel finish is about 80% remaining, it shows use which is to be expected for a 103 year old gun included is the period holster.  Because of the rarity of this conversion this Colt would make a nice addition to your Colt collection.
 
Before his death on June 12, 1945 H J Fitzgerald travelled 30,000 miles a year throughout the U.S. visiting different Police Departments offering Pistol shooting instruction. During these trips he also met with many other clients interested in his shooting skills and his unique conversions including troops during WWII. There’s a possibly this might be one of his conversions since not all his conversions were done at the factory while he worked for Colt; you be the Judge either way these conversions are extremely rare.
 
 $450 OBO, call Bill REDACTED. Will trade for an original Russian AKS with no add on’s. NO TEXTING.

Additional features include: The ability to insert magazines straight into the magazine well (AR Style) without the need to cant the magazine (AK Style); RPK style Windage adjustable rear sights; Windage and elevation adjustable front sights integrated to the gas block; Picatinny rail incorporated into the hinged dust cover (allows optics mounting); and chrome lined chamber, barrel, gas block, and bolt carrier operation rod for increased corrosion and wear resistance.All Factory Manufactured:Left-side folding tubular buttstock with cheek rest and sling loop, competition magazine well, factory 5-round magazine, RPK style windage adjustable rear sight, hinged dust cover with a Picatinny rail, original AK enhanced safety lever (single finger operation), factory chrome line barrel, chamber, receiver shaft, and gas chamber, factory last round bolt hold open, factory threaded barrel, factory machined bolt assembly, and gas blocks. US factory made parts: polymer lower handguard and upper handguard, pistol grip, trigger, hammer, disconnector, and gas puck.SpecificationsCaliber  12 Gauge  Chamber  3" / 76mm  Total Length  38 1/2" / 978mm  Length Folded  28.7" / 728mm  Barrel Length   19" / 483mm   Weight without Magazine   9.7 lbs / 4.4kg  Magazine   Removable box 5 rounds

Cheekpiece/Handgrips: • Cheekpiece infinitely adjustable within range (1” travel). • Cheekpiece can be quickly removed and re-installed, uses a clamp and thumbscrew design. • Includes a simple feature to make the cheekpiece return to the exact height you set it. • Cheekpiece can be moved forward or backward with one alternate position. • Cheekpiece made of polymer to not transmit heat to or away from your face. • Small grips are standard fitment. The larger grip size is an option during checkout or in our Products/Accessories section of the website. Length of Pull (LOP): • Adjustable with spacers in 3/8" increments with nearly 2 1/4” of adjustment range. • LOP range varies slightly between versions but is roughly 12.7” to 15” (technically even longer is possible with even more spacers). • X-Ray's include our 1-3 LOP kit which includes 3 spacers and the hardware to mount either 1, 2, or 3 allowing a max LOP of about 13.8" Buttstock: • Reinforced polymer material. • Heavy internal ribbing provides great strength. • Mounting points for external QD cup or for our Sling Loop/QD mount on either side. • Built in thumbshelf for same-side-thumb-grip shooters. • Entire buttstock assembly can be used on Whiskey-3 if you should desire. Buttpad: • High Quality Kick-EEZ pad with vertical adjustability to various established positions. • Adjusted with hex wrench. • Buttpad is Remington 700 pattern so user can install aftermarket pre-fit pads. Mounting features for slings, monopods, etc: • Buttstock has one position on each side for external QD cup and one position on each side for Sling Loop/QD mount (optional accessories). • Buttstock includes bag rider/butthook which can be replaced with included picatinny rail. • Harris bipod stud included on forend. • Spigot Mount can be added to front of chassis. • Ambi QD sling plate can be mounted and provides 3 positions for QD sling or HK hook sling attachments. Optional Accessories: • Large selection of accessories from sling mounts to tripod mounts. • ALL STOCKS COMES WITH ONE EACH MOE L2 and L3 RAIL. Materials/Finishes: • Most aluminum parts are hard anodized (Type III). • All fasteners are stainless steel, some with black oxide coating, some are without. • Steel parts are salt bath nitrided or stainless steel. • Grip panels, forend, buttstock are injection molded reinforced polymer. Weight: • 3.1 lbs w/o magazine.

Standard Manufacturing Company has raised the bar with this extraordinary shotgun that truly is one of kind that was manufactured in a state of the art facility. The innovative design and guaranteed functionality is well ahead of its time. Extreme detail has been a priority from conception through production of these double barrel repeater shotguns. 

The first of its kind, a premium defense, double barreled, pump, 12 gauge shotgun that quickly fires 16 rounds. Designed for the most discerning shooters who demand extreme firepower and require consistent reliability. The stock has a QR code you can scan with your smart phone or tablet to down load the manual and other information. Please be sure and fill out the warranty card and send it to Standard Manufacturing. 

The spreader choke tubes are designed to shoot a devastating pattern at 25 yards. The choke tubes have Tru-Choke thread patterns. Some pictures show door breachers, these are sold separately. 

The DP-12 provides accessory rails and slots that allow you to customize it with your own accessories. 

Specifications and Features: 
* FDE
* 12 Gauge
* Fires 2 3/4 or 3" shells
* Two 18 7/8" barrels
* 29.5" overall length
* Unloaded weight is 9 pounds 12 ounces
* 16 Round capacity, 14 rounds in the magazines and two rounds in the chamber
* Two shots with each pump
* Single trigger 
* Machined from aircraft grade 7075 aluminum
* Thermal coated receiver
* Inline feeding 
* Ambidextrous safety
* Ambidextrous pump slide release
* Two Picatinny rails for accessories; seven slot rail on the bottom by the foregrip and a 13.75" 34 slot rail on top 
* Co-Molded non-slip rubber grip 
* Slots to attach MOE rails
* Shell indicator window 
* Shock absorbing spring loaded recoil mechanism
* Synthetic stock 
* Rubber recoil pad with dual spring loaded recoil
* Both barrels include spreader choke tubes with Tru-Choke thread pattern
* Choke tube wrench 
* Heavy duty lock
* Instruction booklet and warranty card
* Composite foregrip 
* Front sling attachment 
* Sling swivel attachment on stock
* Erogonomically designed to balance the weight of a loaded gun for quick and efficient handling with minimal recoil
